[1]
Date: Sun 22 Jan 2012
Source: Xinhua English News [edited]
http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/china/2012-01/22/c_131373430.htm


Man dies of bird flu in south west China
----------------------------------------
Beijing: A 39 year old man died of highly pathogenic avian influenza (H5N1) [virus infection] in south west China on Sunday [22 Jan 2012], the Ministry of Health said.

The man, who began to suffer from fever on 6 Jan 2012, died at noon on Sunday [22 Jan 2012] in a hospital in Guiyang, capital of Guizhou Province, after being treated with intensive care for 3 days, the ministry said. The disease control and prevention centers at both the provincial and national levels have confirmed the [diagnosis] of H5N1 infection.

Up to now, the 71 individuals who have been in close contact with the victim have not shown unusual symptoms, the ministry said.

--
