[2]
Date: Sun 22 Jan 2012
Source: RTHK English News [edited]
http://rthk.hk/rthk/news/englishnews/20120122/news_20120122_56_813515.htm


Man dies of H5N1 bird flu in Guizhou
------------------------------------
The mainland authorities say a man has died of H5N1 bird flu in Guizhou province, and they have notified the Centre for Health Protection in Hong Kong. The centre said the patient was a 39 year old man who developed symptoms on 6 Jan 2012 and was admitted to hospital the same day.

The man did not report having been in contact with poultry before the onset of symptoms.

Last month, a 39 year old man in Shenzhen died after being diagnosed with bird flu. The authorities there said at the time that he hadn't had any direct contact with poultry during the previous month. But a specialist in infectious diseases, Dr Lo Wing-lok, said poultry should still be suspected as the probable source of infection.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Mary Marshall

[If confirmed by WHO this will bring the total number of cases of avian A/(H5N1) influenza virus infection in China to 42 with 28 fatalities. There was a single case in 2003, 8 in 2005, 13 in 2006, 5 in 2007, 4 in 2008, 7 in 2009, 2 in 2010, 1 in 2011, and 1 so far in 2012.

A map of the provinces of China, showing Guizhou in the south, can be accessed at http://www.muztagh.com/map-of-china/. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1zaU.]
